{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778261671,"nonce":"qxlbZmtgIxH/N8erlHRF0glSWgI=","title":"Phase umbrella: regulator-coupling and biomechanical decoupling — staged programme","message":"## Motivating question\n\nWhy does our trained flavor-B controller give Δv ≈ −25% while the corrected analytical H∞ Riccati gives Δv ≈ +1–2.4% on the C\u0026S regime, and what does that disagreement tell us about the relationship between linear-controller theory and trained recurrent controllers under unpredictable disturbances?\n\n## Status\n\n**Exploring**, not yet committed. This umbrella defines a candidate next phase for the project; the user has not yet greenlit running the chain end-to-end. Stages can be paused after each if the answer is decisive.\n\n## Headline puzzle\n\n| Source | Δv at 1.5γ* | sign |\n|---|---|---|\n| C\u0026S 2019 (Fig 1e visual) | ~+10–15% | + |\n| Our analytical Riccati (corrected, full-state B_w) | +1.00% / +1.53% / +2.35% (C\u0026S regime / near γ* / rlrmp regime) | + |\n| Our trained flavor-B controllers (empirical) | −20.75% / −26.40% / −25.68% (η=0.03/0.10/0.30) | **−** |\n\nBimodal replicate distribution: ~25% of replicates at +40 to +57%, the rest negative.\n\n## Reframing — regulator vs tracker, not linear vs nonlinear\n\nTwo outside agents (Codex, Gemini) diagnosed this in May 2026. Their disagreement clarified the load-bearing question. The key insight (independent reviewer, plan doc): the right architectural cut is *regulator* (`u_t = -K_t · x_t`) vs *tracker* (`u_t = u_ff(t) - K_t · (x_t - x_nom(t))`). Linear regulator and linear tracker have similar expressivity but a tracker decouples nominal-drive from feedback-stiffness; a regulator cannot. The decoupling hypothesis attributes our Δv ≈ 0 finding to RNN-as-tracker behaviour.\n\n## 4-cell discriminator (Stage 2)\n\n| | regulator (`u = -K_t·x`) | tracker (`u_ff + K_t·error`) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Gemini-right (decoupling-is-real) | +Δv | ≈0 |\n| Gemini-wrong (schedule-driven Δv) | +Δv | +Δv |\n| Training broken | ≈0 | ≈0 |\n\n## 9-stage chain\n\n(Stage IDs reference child issues. Stage 5 reuses existing `db35426`.)\n\n0. **`03a148a`** — Replicate C\u0026S 2019 LQG vs H∞ Riccati directly. Prerequisite for all downstream comparisons; produces the analytical baseline.\n1. **`4469cae`** — Eval-pipeline correction. Re-evaluate analytical Riccati on 0.5 m geometry; document and either fix or relabel the trained-controller eval.\n2. **`d448c9d`** — Linear regulator + linear tracker baselines under matched ε-adversary and matched (t/N)^6 Q schedule. The decoupling acid test (4-cell above).\n3. **`6ec6b19`** — Cost-schedule sweep `(t/N)^α` for α ∈ {0,1,2,4,6,10} on Riccati and on each architecture. Quantifies how much of Δv is schedule-driven.\n4. **`020a65b`** — Full-state ε adversary class matching C\u0026S Eq. 13. Round-trip identity: linear regulator under matched ε must converge to analytical Riccati.\n5. **`db35426`** — H∞ Riccati teacher distillation (existing issue). Capacity check: can the GRU represent the velocity-inflation policy?\n6. **`cf56e1e`** — Capacity-restricted RNN ablation (rank-1 → full GRU). Where on the expressivity ladder does decoupling kick in?\n7. **`ac06736`** — Two-link arm with 6-muscle dynamics. Tests biomechanical-coupling story.\n8. **`8fcb6c7`** — Decoupling decomposition analysis (variance partition `u_ff + K_local·error + residual`). The internal interpretability check.\n9. **`f7b1b17`** — Constrained-RNN regulator (no `u_ff` channel). If we force regulator form, do we recover Δv \u003e 0?\n\n## Cross-cutting\n\n- **`daa48c8`** — Bimodal-replicate analysis. Apply across all stages; do not collapse Δv to group means without cluster-conditioning.\n\n## Per-stage predicted-outcomes table\n\n| Stage | Gemini (decoupling-is-real) | Codex (underdetermined; confounds dominate) | What would falsify both |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 (eval audit) | trained Δv stays ≈ −25% after geometry/schedule fix | trained Δv shifts toward zero or positive | trained Δv shifts to *highly negative* (−60%+); means a deeper bug |\n| 2 (linear regulator vs tracker) | regulator: +Δv; tracker, RNN: ≈ 0 | all four split unpredictably; possibly all near 0 due to other confounds | all four converge to the same Δv (controller class doesn't matter) |\n| 3 (Q-schedule sweep) | RNN's Δv stays flat across α; regulator's Δv tracks Riccati | RNN tracks Riccati under matched α | both architectures stay at Δv ≈ 0 across α (schedule isn't the driver either) |\n| 4 (matched ε-adversary) | linear regulator → +Δv; GRU stays ≈ 0 | linear regulator round-trips cleanly; GRU shifts substantially toward Riccati | round-trip identity fails on the linear regulator (training is broken) |\n| 5 (Riccati distillation) | cloned GRU recovers +Δv (architecture is capable) | cloned GRU recovers +Δv (architecture is capable) | cloned GRU stays ≈ 0 (architecture cannot represent the policy — surprise) |\n| 6 (rank ablation) | smooth shift from regulator-like to tracker-like across rank | unclear; possibly noisy | flat across rank (capacity is not the operative axis) |\n| 7 (muscle plant) | likely Δv goes positive — biology forces coupling | likely Δv stays ≈ 0 — RNN still decouples in muscle space | Δv goes *more* negative (biomechanics suppresses inflation, opposite of human result) |\n| 8 (decomposition) | high `u_ff` variance fraction in GRU; low in linear regulator | mixed; depends on Stage 4 outcome | clean linear regulator-like decomposition in *all* trained networks |\n| 9 (constraint experiments) | constrained GRU recovers +Δv | constrained GRU still ≈ 0 if the issue is loss-side, not architecture-side | constrained GRU recovers +Δv but with grossly degraded loss (the constraint just breaks training) |\n\n## Formal / theorem-shaped avenues (deferred)\n\nNot actionable now — listed for recoverability.\n\n- **Existence of a decoupling separation principle.** Under what conditions on `(A, B, B_w, Q, R, T)` does the Riccati optimal `K_t` admit an exact decomposition `u_t = u_ff(t) - K_local(t)·(x_t - x_nom(t))` with `K_local(t)` strictly less than `K_t` in a Loewner sense? Conjecture: holds whenever the LQ-game value function admits a decomposition into a *steering* term and a *fluctuation* term. Reference template: Anderson \u0026 Moore's separation theorem for LQG, generalised to LQ-games.\n- **Capacity bound on linear-feedback realisability.** Define a \"regulator gap\" as `inf_{u_ff} sup_t || K_t · x_nom(t) - u_ff(t) ||`. For what plant + cost combinations is this gap small (regulators and trackers are equivalent) vs large (only trackers can decouple)? This formalises Gemini's intuition.\n- **Representation theorem for RNN policies as time-varying linear-plus-residual.** Given a GRU trained on a control task with bounded loss, does there exist a universal decomposition `π_RNN(x, h, t) = u_ff_θ(t) + K_θ(t)·(x - x_nom(t)) + ε_θ(x, t, h)` with `||ε||` small? The interesting question is whether SGD under the H∞ loss converges to the tracker form preferentially.\n- **Equivalence of LinearDynamicsAdversary and the H∞ ε-game in a limit.** As inner-PGD step count → ∞ and `η_max` is appropriately scaled, does the constant-`ΔA` Frobenius-bounded adversary converge in distribution to the free-`ε` H∞ adversary? Conjecture: only in the small-`η_max` limit and only on trajectories through generic points of state space.\n- **A \"no-free-lunch\" result for biomechanical decoupling.** Given a plant with antagonist-pair muscle dynamics with metabolic cost convex-quadratic in activation, is there a structural theorem that co-contraction-induced stiffness *must* couple with feedforward drive, in a way that point-mass plants do not? This formalises Codex's biology argument 4.\n- **Information-theoretic bound on velocity inflation.** Under unpredictable disturbances of bounded entropy entering at the velocity channel, does there exist a lower bound on the optimal peak forward velocity of the form `v_peak ≥ v_LQR + f(I(disturbance), reach_geometry)` for some monotonic `f`? This would be a model-free version of the \"robust-must-be-faster\" claim.\n\nThese were previously filed as deferred issue `f6e0cc2`; that issue is now superseded by this umbrella body.\n\n## Killable risks\n\n- **Eval pipeline still buggy after Stage 1.** If `_build_canonical_reach_trial_specs` keeps reusing the wrong trials, every downstream stage is contaminated. Mitigation: write a regression test asserting `trial_specs.init.pos == (0,0)` and `trial_specs.target.pos == (0.15, 0)` exactly after the build step.\n- **Inner-PGD does not converge to the worst-case adversary.** Five inner steps may be insufficient at small `η_max`, contaminating every training run. Mitigation: at Stage 2, sweep PGD inner-step count {5, 20, 50}. (Issue `89891ab` flags this.)\n- **Architecture-capacity ablation dominated by optimiser variance.** Rank-r RNNs may train to different solutions across seeds. Mitigation: ≥ 5 seeds per rank; use bimodal-replicate analysis (`daa48c8`) as the template.\n- **Muscle-plant training unstable.** feedbax's `AnalyticalMusculoskeletalPlant` is less battle-tested; Stage 7 starts with a non-adversarial baseline (\"can we train a GRU in muscle space at all?\") before introducing the ε-adversary.\n- **Bimodality persists across stages.** The −25% group mean hides ~25% of replicates at +40 to +57%. Report cluster-conditioned Δv at every stage; do not collapse to means.\n- **C\u0026S's +10–15% is itself a cherry-picked condition.** Reading C\u0026S Fig 1e visually is not the same as the rlrmp Δv metric. Stage 0 should include a careful re-read of C\u0026S's reported numbers. This is a non-trivial risk: the entire programme treats +10–15% as fixed truth, but it is a single number from a single paper read once.\n- **Compute and human time.** Stages 4, 6, 7 each consume substantial GPU hours; muscle-plant work (Stage 7) likely needs A100/RTX5090-class compute and may take 1–2 weeks to debug.\n\n## Cross-references\n\n- Phases coord: `b33e8da` (this umbrella indexed there)\n- Training-methods coord: `c99ad9d` (training-method aspects of Stages 2, 4, 6, 7, 9)\n- Analyses coord: `4d38c15` (new analyses: Stage 1 audit, Stage 8 decomposition, capacity ablation, bimodal)\n- Synthesis doc: `results/flavor_a_vs_b/synthesis.md` §8.0–8.0.1\n- Plan doc (planning artifact, not tracked): `tmp/flavor_ab_review/decoupling_chain_plan.md`","files":null}]}